Description: Brn Tabby / Tortie Spayed Female Domestic Shorthair Cat

Age: 1 YEAR 2 MONTHS

Current Location: In RASKC Foster Home

My name is Samara and I am a somewhat petite girl, weighing about 9 pounds. I am a little over a year old. I came to the shelter as a stray with a broken leg. So I have had time in a foster home to heal up before I am adopted. After my leg healed I have been just fine, without any deformity or problems related to it. The good part is that since I have been in foster care they know a lot about me, my personality and habits. It makes it much less of an unknown for anyone who wants to adopt me.

So here's what my foster mom says about me: "Samara is a somewhat timid girl at times and walks or runs away when approached with the following exceptions,1) is when I'm in the kitchen - she's a good eater and always up for food, even rubs against my legs and lets me pet her. 2)The other instance is if she's lying on a chair or couch or on the cat tree. I can walk up to her and pet her and she purrs up a storm. She will even lie on my lap. She gets along with my two senior boy cats. She has not been around dogs at my house. She's very good with the litter box."

So that is what my foster mom says. Now, since I am a bit on the timid side at times(all of us cats have our own unique personalities) it would be best to be in a quiet household where if children are present they will be respectful of my need to have my own personal space. I will need time to adjust to a new family. I have my vaccinations,am microchipped and am healthy...now all I need is my own family. Please ask to see me, you will get yourself one wonderful cat!

Adoption Fee: An Adoption Fee has not been set. Please inquire with the shelter.

Memo:
Received on: 2017-02-14

Description: Gray

Neutered Male Terrier Dog

Age: 1 YEAR 10 MONTHS

Current Location: Kirkland Petco 12040 NE 85TH ST KIRKLAND, WA 98033

Hi! My name is Otis and I am available for adoption at the Eastside Pet Adoption Center inside the Kirkland Petco. I am about one and a half years old and have a cute, scruffy gray terrier coat. You can also find me by my ID #A470418.

I was brought into the shelter by my previous adopter on February 14, 2017 because I was not the best fit for their household. I need a dog savvy and experience owner that understands how scary the world can be for a little guy like me and can slowly gain my trust. I would also do best in an adult only home and with another social dog or multiple dogs in my home that will show me the ropes and who I can follow around and mimic.

I am very easily spooked and frightened in new situations and with new people. I love treats though and I am slowly improving as shelter staff and volunteers work with me. I will need a family who is willing to go at my pace and be very patient. On the other end, I need an owner that will encourage me to push my boundaries and safely become more confident.

It will still take me time to continue to gain more confidence, but I seem to enjoy being around people and I have lots of potential! I am a very sweet boy when I warm up to you and I love playing when comfortable!

I still need a lot of work getting used to walking on leash. I still sometimes dart away from people, so I should not be allowed to roam a yard off-leash but access to a fully secure, fenced yard will help me become more and more comfortable on leash at my own pace.

Once I am comfortable in the home, I have displayed some separation anxiety related behaviors. I am looking for a family familiar with working with a dog with separation anxiety. Having another dog in the home may also help reduce my anxiety when my people are not around.

If you would like more information about me, please call (425) 406-8081 or come to the Eastside Pet Adoption Center inside the Kirkland Petco to meet me!

Adoption Fee: $200.00
